        "name": "Current Global Conflicts 2025 — Live War Map & Market Impact",
        "description": "Comprehensive tracker of every active global conflict in 2025 and 2026, with risk scoring, market impact analysis, and geopolitical intelligence.",
        "isPartOf": { "@id": "https://www.orreryx.io" },
        "primaryImageOfPage": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.orreryx.io/og-default.png" },
        "dateModified": "2026-04-17",
        "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Orrery", "url": "https://www.orreryx.io" },
        "publisher": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": "Orrery",
          "url": "https://www.orreryx.io",
          "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.orreryx.io/favicon.ico" }
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How many active global conflicts are there in 2025?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "As of 2025, there are more than 50 ongoing armed conflicts worldwide, with approximately 7 classified as major wars involving more than 1,000 battle-related deaths per year. The most significant include Ukraine-Russia, Israel-Gaza, Sudan, Myanmar, and the DRC. The Uppsala Conflict Data Program reports this represents the highest concentration of active conflicts since World War II."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Which current conflict has the highest market impact in 2025?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "The Ukraine-Russia war continues to have the highest direct market impact in 2025, primarily through energy prices (European natural gas), global wheat and grain supplies, and NATO defense spending. The Israel-Gaza conflict ranks second for market impact, with ripple effects through Middle East oil supply routes, Red Sea shipping disruptions, and regional currency stability."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do global conflicts affect the stock market?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Global conflicts affect markets through multiple channels: energy price spikes (oil and gas), commodity disruptions (wheat, copper, rare earths), supply chain rerouting costs, flight-to-safety flows into gold and USD, increased defense spending (boosting defense stocks), and risk-off sentiment causing broad equity sell-offs. The VIX (volatility index) typically spikes 20-40% within days of major conflict escalations."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the safest investment during global conflicts?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Historically, gold is the top-performing asset during geopolitical crises, rising an average of 8-15% in the 6 months following major conflict escalations. US Treasury bonds (flight-to-safety), USD cash positions, Swiss franc, and defense sector ETFs (XAR, ITA) also outperform during conflict periods. Energy commodities like crude oil and natural gas spike initially but can reverse sharply once conflicts stabilize."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is WW3 starting because of current conflicts in 2025?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Major geopolitical analysts do not classify current conflicts as the beginning of World War 3, though the risk is higher than at any point since the Cold War. The Bulletin of Atomic Scientists' Doomsday Clock stood at 89 seconds to midnight as of early 2025 — the closest ever recorded. Key escalation risks include NATO-Russia direct engagement in Ukraine, China-Taiwan military action, and Iran-Israel confrontation expanding into a regional war."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
          { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.orreryx.io" },
